    isValidName

    public static boolean isValidName(String name)
    According to the HTML spec, ID must begin with a letter A-Za-z, and may be followed by any number of [a-zA-Z0-9-_:.]. It is not spelled out what is allowed in class, but we are assuming the same is true there.

    Returns:
    Whether the string is a valid ID for HTML purposes.
